  "prompt": "What is the dress code for fresher girls in Capgemini?",
  "response": "Capgemini typically recommends a professional and formal business attire for female employees during the initial training and work period. The standard dress code usually includes:\n\n1. Professional Western Formals:\n- Formal shirts or blouses\n- Trousers or knee-length skirts\n- Blazers or formal jackets\n- Comfortable closed shoes\n\n2. Color Suggestions:\n- Neutral colors like white, black, gray, navy blue\n- Pastel shades\n- Avoid very bright or flashy colors\n\n3. General Guidelines:\n- Neat and clean appearance\n- Minimal and professional makeup\n- Simple and professional jewelry\n- Well-maintained hairstyle\n\n4. Important Notes:\n- Avoid revealing or tight-fitting clothes\n- Maintain a formal and professional look\n- Follow specific instructions provided during orientation\n\nHowever, for the most accurate and current dress code, it's best to:\n- Check your joining letter\n- Consult HR during orientation\n- Ask current employees or your recruitment point of contact\n\nThe exact dress code might vary slightly between different Capgemini offices and locations.",
